cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC, cs.SD 

This paper deals with the interpretation of non-sentential utterances in dialogue, which is a problem in computational linguistics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning experiments and probabilistic rules, which suggest that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with dialogue state and dynamics, which could place it in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.SD (Sound).
